column2: UPDATE 1-Activision says U.S. court stops $8.2 bln deal with Vivendi SAN FRANCISCO
column3: Sept 18 A U.S. court has handed down a preliminary decision to halt the closing of Vivendi SA's  $8.2 billion deal to sell most of its stake in Activision Blizzard Inc back to the U.S. company
column4: the games publisher said on Wednesday.

column2: General Dynamics wins $188 mln Saudi tank order -Pentagon WASHINGTON
column3: Sept 18 General Dynamics Corp  has won a $187.5 million contract to upgrade 44 M1A1 Abrams tanks and 40 M1A2-model Abrams tanks for Saudi Arabia
column4: the Pentagon announced Wednesday.

column2: GE to take 2 cent/share charge related to Avio dealUPDATE 1-General Electric names new head of oil and gas unit Sept 18 General Electric Co on Wednesday named Lorenzo Simonelli as chief executive of its oil and gas unit
column3: replacing Dan Heintzelman
column4: who was appointed a vice chairman of the company.  UPDATE 1-General Electric names new head of oil and gas unit Sept 18 General Electric Co on Wednesday named Lorenzo Simonelli as chief executive of its oil and gas unit
column6: who was appointed a vice chairman of the company. General Electric Co  said it would take a charge of 2 cents per share related to its $4.3 billion acquisition of the aeronautical unit of Italian aerospace company Avio SpA.UPDATE 1-General Electric names new head of oil and gas unit Sept 18 General Electric Co on Wednesday named Lorenzo Simonelli as chief executive of its oil and gas unit
